race.comment: MYRIAD (2) former Godolphin three-year-old resuming for the Nathan Doyle stable. Gelded over the break after failing to show much in three runs in Victoria. Has impressed in two searching 1000m trials and no shock to see him prove too good for these. EX WIFE (1) had mixed fortunes in three runs this campaign and now in the Glen Milligan yard. Faded quickly in town with the 59kg when a poor last over 1300m at Warwick Farm. Improver at this level. RED CHICK (8) chipped away late on debut when fourth over 1015m at Grafton. Fitter now and can race closer from the low gate. CLUSTER'S GENERAL (7) solid return over the 810m with the 59kg for a courageous third at Coffs Harbour. Only has to hold that form to take a hand in the finish.
